https://www.weather.gov/media/pah/WeatherEducation/stormbased.pdf
"On October 1st, 2007, the National Weather Service introduced Storm Based Warnings for tornadoes, severe
thunderstorms, flash floods and marine hazards that are more geographically specific for these short-duration weather
events."

so 2008 is the first full calendar year with warning polygons

warning polygons are from IEM (public domain)...see the "iem requst N.png" files for the exact dataset requests
https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/request/gis/watchwarn.phtml